node.title: 'Expect long delays': Part of SH1 closed in both directions after Auckland crash leaves person dead
node.description: Drivers are urged to consider SH16 as an alternative route or to expect long delays.
node.content: ["Drivers in north Auckland have been told to expect long delays after a fatal crash closed a large section of State Highway 1.", "Police are currently in attendance at the two-vehicle crash, which occurred on a section of SH1 just south of Warkworth on Friday afternoon, after being called to the scene at 1:38pm.", "One person was initially assessed to be in a critical condition, but police later confirmed they had died at the scene. Another person is in a serious condition and will be transported to hospital.", "Newshub has contacted St John for an update.", "The New Zealand Transport Agency Waka Kotahi (NZTA) says the SH1 closure extends from Grand Dr in Orewa to Woodcocks Rd in Warkworth.", "\"Motorists are advised to delay their journey or use SH16 via Kaukapakapa as an alternate route,\" the agency said in a statement. \"The road is likely to remain closed for some time today as a serious crash investigation takes place.\"", "Police say the Serious Crash Unit has been notified and will be examining the scene.", "\"An investigation will be commenced into the circumstances of the crash. Police continue to advise motorists heading north and south to expect delays to their journeys this evening.\""]
